There is alive the spirit of independence and the deep desire to tell a story with a singular voice that speaks of our human existence... The film selected is a beautifully expressed film in many, many ways - including the cinematography. The shadow and the light in the images played as much a part in telling the story as the acting and the text. Deftly using color palette, texture, and a shallow depth of field, the cinematographer imbued the images with a dramatic resonance to the imagery, while the handheld gave the film an engaged, intimate feel.
